We only recognize as paid‐in capital the owner’s injections at the very start. In the provided transactions the transactions that represent equity injections (all with the same “Initial20231231001” id) are these three lines:

• Cash deposit of 3,000,000.0  
• Bank deposit of 5,000,000.0  
• Fixed Assets contributed at 8,000,000.0

Adding these gives:
  3,000,000.0 + 5,000,000.0 + 8,000,000.0 = 16,000,000.0

Since none of the other transactions (purchases, sales, expenses, or depreciation) are owner contributions or withdrawals, they do not affect the paid‐in capital. Therefore, both the initial paid‐in capital and the ending paid‐in capital remain 16,000,000.00.
